<div id="Bulking_Lottie" class="mx-auto d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center"></div>
<div class="bulking" align="center">
    <br/>
    <h1>Bulking Joureny</h1>
    <p>

        Bulking is a phase in bodybuilding and fitness where individuals aim to gain muscle mass and size by consuming a 
        calorie surplus.
        It is a very common goal amongst fitness enthusiasts and a fundamental part of muscle building. However, 
        bulking is not as simple as eating everything in sight. It requires a strategic approach and a well-structured 
        plan to maximize muscle growth while minimizing fat gain. 
    </p>

    <br/>
    <h1>What to eat when bulking?</h1>
    <br/>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <h2>Nutrient Categories</h2>
                <hr />
                <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Category</th>
                        <th>Foods</th>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Lean Proteins -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Lean Proteins
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Chicken breast</li>
                                <li>Turkey</li>
                                <li>Fish (salmon, tuna, tilapia)</li>
                                <li>Lean cuts of beef or pork</li>
                                <li>Eggs and egg whites</li>
                                <li>Plant-based proteins (tofu, tempeh, legumes)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Complex Carbohydrates -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Complex Carbohydrates
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Whole grains (brown rice, quinoa, oats, whole wheat)</li>
                                <li>Potatoes and sweet potatoes</li>
                                <li>Beans and lentils</li>
                                <li>Pasta and whole grain bread</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Healthy Fats -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Healthy Fats
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Avocados</li>
                                <li>Nuts and seeds (almonds, walnuts, chia seeds)</li>
                                <li>Olive oil</li>
                                <li>Fatty fish (salmon, mackerel)</li>
                                <li>Nut butters (peanut butter, almond butter)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Dairy and Alternatives -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Dairy and Alternatives
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Greek yogurt</li>
                                <li>Milk (including alternatives like almond or soy milk)</li>
                                <li>Cottage cheese</li>
                                <li>Cheese</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Fruits -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Fruits
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Berries (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries)</li>
                                <li>Bananas</li>
                                <li>Apples</li>
                                <li>Oranges</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Vegetables -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Vegetables
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Broccoli</li>
                                <li>Spinach</li>
                                <li>Kale</li>
                                <li>Brussels sprouts</li>
                                <li>Bell peppers</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Hydration -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Hydration
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Water is essential for overall health and can aid digestion.</li>
                                <li>Fruit juices and smoothies can contribute to calorie intake.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Snacks -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Snacks
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Protein bars</li>
                                <li>Trail mix with nuts and dried fruits</li>
                                <li>Greek yogurt with granola</li>
                                <li>Hard-boiled eggs</li>
                                <li>Hummus with whole-grain crackers or vegetables</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                    <!-- Meal Timing -->
                    <tr>
                        <td>
                            Meal Timing
                        </td>
                        <td>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Consume balanced meals with a mix of proteins, carbohydrates, and fats.</li>
                                <li>Consider pre- and post-workout nutrition for energy and recovery.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </td>
                    </tr>

                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

